{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/hiccups/how-this-topic-was-developed/declarations-of-interest/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"92541ea8-a332-5c95-8861-4266932eeb03","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 8241c26e-21b9-43fe-a9f7-a7f3001712ad --><h2>Declarations of interest</h2><!-- end field 8241c26e-21b9-43fe-a9f7-a7f3001712ad -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f84c0bdf-8f71-4bd7-8388-a7f30015bd73 --><!-- begin field b1c58e7b-404a-47f7-8fbe-a7f3001712ad --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field b1c58e7b-404a-47f7-8fbe-a7f3001712ad --><!-- begin field c44ad9e4-b9a6-4ff5-8566-a7f3001712ad --><p>Clarity Informatics requests that all those involved in the writing and reviewing of topics, and those involved in the external review process to declare any competing interests. Signed copies are securely held by Clarity Informatics and are available on request with the permission of the individual. A copy of the declaration of interest form which participants are asked to complete annually is also available on request. A brief outline of the declarations of interest policy is described here and full details of the policy is available on the <a href=\"https://cks.clarity.co.uk/\" data-hyperlink-id=\"00fd8df7-8f9e-4db3-a24c-a99200454225\">Clarity Informatics website</a>. Declarations of interests of the authors are not routinely published, however competing interests of all those involved in the topic update or development are listed below. Competing interests include:</p><ul><li>Personal financial interests</li><li>Personal family interest</li><li>Personal non-financial interest</li><li>Non-personal financial gain or benefit</li></ul><p>Although particular attention is given to interests that could result in financial gains or losses for the individual, competing interests may also arise from academic competition or for political, personal, religious, and reputational reasons. An individual is not obliged to seek out knowledge of work done for, or on behalf of, the healthcare industry within the departments for which they are responsible if they would not normally expect to be informed.</p><!-- end field c44ad9e4-b9a6-4ff5-8566-a7f3001712ad --><!-- begin field fe0a3603-9842-4a64-956f-a7f3001712ad --><h2>Who should declare competing interests?</h2><!-- end field fe0a3603-9842-4a64-956f-a7f3001712ad --><!-- begin field 708b2c9c-4a04-4dc6-8cea-a7f3001712ad --><p>Any individual (or organization) involved in developing, reviewing, or commenting on clinical content, particularly the recommendations should declare competing interests. This includes the authoring team members, expert advisers, external reviewers of draft topics, individuals providing feedback on published topics, and Editorial Steering Group members. Declarations of interest are completed annually for authoring team and editorial steering group members, and are completed at the start of the topic update and development process for external stakeholders.</p><!-- end field 708b2c9c-4a04-4dc6-8cea-a7f3001712ad --><!-- begin field cd75e11f-7ad0-4637-b715-a7f3001712ad --><h2>Competing interests declared for this topic:</h2><!-- end field cd75e11f-7ad0-4637-b715-a7f3001712ad --><!-- begin field a77dab81-178c-464f-9541-a7f3001712ad --><p>None.</p><!-- end field a77dab81-178c-464f-9541-a7f3001712ad --><!-- end item f84c0bdf-8f71-4bd7-8388-a7f30015bd73 -->","topic":{"id":"ba8226ed-5a0f-5ab1-a1e1-dcfae8000926","topicId":"c41b31d9-94df-45b7-ae5b-6afc3d892e11","topicName":"Hiccups","slug":"hiccups","lastRevised":"Last revised in JuneÂ 2017","chapters":[{"id":"4a69af5e-7c46-5a5f-8e8a-90fa4de90fc4","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"b5728539-44d6-546a-bd7f-298976ccc9f2","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"914a226b-c27c-